{"questionId":"32478311","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The equations <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>y</mi></math> can be written in matrix form as</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">M</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>x</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>y</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">A manufacturer wants to compare two springs, Spring 1 and Spring 2, that could be used as shock absorbers.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The differential equation for Spring 1 has <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>77</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">For these values, the eigenvalues of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">M</mi></math> are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>11</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the corresponding eigenvectors.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>77</mn></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>18</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>x</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>y</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>x</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>y</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> &nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>77</mn></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>18</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>x</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>y</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>11</mn><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>x</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>y</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> <em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p>eigenvector is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; (or any multiple)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>11</mn><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p>eigenvector is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>11</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; (or any multiple)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>